OL,3,CRedundancies made at Lindsey oil
OL,4,Crefinery as bids considered for the
OL,5,Csite
OL,7,F"The government had promised to ensure
OL,8,Fthat job focused bids would be the
OL,9,Fpriority at Lindsey, yet prior to bids
OL,10,Feven being considered, they are
OL,11,Falready issuing redundancy notices.
OL,13,F"Unless Labour start to back workers
OL,14,Fand British industry it will continue
OL,15,Fto haemorrhage support."
OL,17,FIn a statement, Energy Minister,
OL,18,FMicheal Shanks expressed his thoughts
OL,19,Ffor the community and families
OL,20,Faffected, highlighting it was a
OL,21,Fdecision Prax made itself.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOUwD@XO]
